Giant Bay ResourcesLtd said a metallurgical study of its Gordon Lake gold depositindicated an overall recovery of 95 pct to 96 pct of the goldcan be achieved by either direct cyanidation of ore orflotation followed by cyanidation of concentrate.    Continuation of an underground program on the property willbegin in June, extending an existing drift along the200-foot-level where the main ore zone was encountered, GiantBay said.    The company did not elaborate on production figures for theproperty. Reuter&#3;